							</span>
			<a href="http://werblog.com/2005/09/the-great-internet-transformation-a-first-stab/#comment-58" class="social-posted-when" target="_blank">September 21, 2005</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="social-comment-body">
				<p>I&#8217;m interested what &#8220;light-weight innovation&#8221; might mean in terms of profit making potential, versus &#8220;heavy weight&#8221; in terms of traditional strategy thinking on barriers to entry and exit, ease of substitution, access to unique resources, vertical integration, and path dependencies (i.e. I can&#8217;t do this job, because I haven&#8217;t learned the know how my competitor has, because he competed in the previous generation). Might be an interesting angle on who needs who under future scenarios.<br />
Just A thought.</p>
<p>Regards</p>
